        <abstract> 
<p>Is obliged for the facts about the hybrids [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">5910</hi>], which permit him to reject the view of B. D. Walsh (and H. W. Bates?) that organs play an important part in keeping incipient species distinct.</p>  
<p>He has asked John Murray to send RM a copy of <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
